-## 2. Granular Task-Level Boundaries
-
-This table lists specific tasks to help you identify whether a piece of work belongs to you or another team member:
-
-| Task Instance | **Who Actually Codes It?** | **Why It Is NOT Your Job** |
-| --- | --- | --- |
-| **Generating Raw Data** | **Nicole Adhiambo** (Data Scientist) | As a Backend Developer, you establish the database structure and ingestion endpoint (`POST /ingest`). Nicole writes the `Faker`/`SDV` scripts that generate the data to put *into* your endpoint. |
-| **Tuning AI & Forecasting Models** | **Gavinta Tipape & Jesse Ng'eno** (AI/ML) | You import their finalized logic into a background task wrapper inside your services folder. You do **not** configure model hyperparameters, tweak train/test splits, or write raw predictive model training logic. |
-| **Drafting Medical Content & Briefs** | **Fatoumata Bintou & Mentors** (Domain Experts) | You map the structured JSON data schema that paths the advisory briefs. The actual medical content, treatment recommendations, and guideline text come from Fatoumata and your clinical mentors. |
-| **Writing Dashboard Components** | **Lowell Owuor** (Frontend) | You provide the secure JSON payloads for the maps and charts via `GET` requests. Lowell handles visual styling, CSS rendering, React states, and interactive user interface layouts. |
